        <h2>Common Issues with Avantco Ice Machines</h2>
        <p>Avantco Ice machines require regular servicing to prevent malfunctions. Some of the most common issues include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice machine not making ice</strong> – Could be due to a faulty water inlet valve, clogged filter, or a failing compressor.</li>
            <li><strong>Slow ice production</strong> – Commonly caused by dirty condenser coils, low water pressure, or a malfunctioning thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice machine leaking water</strong> – Often the result of a damaged pump, improper drainage, or cracked water lines.</li>
            <li><strong>Irregularly shaped ice cubes</strong> – Indicates issues with water flow, freezing cycle, or ice mold thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Excessive noise during operation</strong> – Can be caused by worn-out fan motors, loose components, or faulty bearings.</li>
        </ul>
        
